metadata.name: mtnman's pfp
metadata.description:
Most of you will never read this, but if you do you're probably wondering why I minted a derivative of my ape (BAYC 2465) to use as my Twitter pfp. 

What can I say? I like the hexagon.

I'm tired of my pfp reverting to a circle whenever I move my ape and I have no intention of connecting my vault to Twitter. So here we are, with this derivative of BAYC 2465.
